	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Julia sets and Mandelbrot sets are calculated with the same recurrence relation
<br />
<br />z[n+1] = z[n]^2 + c
<br />
<br />For the Mandlebrot set, z[0] = 0 and c varies over the entire complex plane.
<br />
<br />For Julia sets, a specific complex value c is selected, and z[0] varies over the entire complex plane.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
